ken to reduce worst effects. As a diagnostic method, RTM offers a statistically valid way to identify vulnerable places. To learn more, visit http://www.riskterrainmodeling.com and begin using RTM with the many free tutorials and resources.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCrime analysisxStatistical methods. 0aCrime forecastingxGeographic information systems. 0aCrime prevention. 0aCrimexEnvironmental aspects. 0aSpatial analysis (Statistics). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  acontexts of crime.  acrime emergence.  acrime exposure.  acrime persistence.  acrime prediction.  acrime.  acriminal behavior.  acriminals.  acustom strategies.  aexposure.  aforecasting crimes.  aidentifying risk.  aminimizing risk.  amodeling methods.  arisk management.  arisk reduction.  artm.  aspatial dynamics of crime.  asurveillance.  atheory of risky places.  avulnerable places.1 aKennedy, Leslie W., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028293340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095880740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520958807423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520958807/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY